          <title>US aid freeze puts HIV-positive orphans in Kenya at risk as medical supplies dwindle</title>
          <description><![CDATA[NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) — Two-year-old Evans was brought to the Nyumbani Children’s Home in Nairobi, Kenya a year ago, suffering from HIV and tuberculosis. With no family to care for him, Evans was referred to the orphanage by a health center after he stopped responding to medical treatment.]]></description>
